entry.value: select * from FLOWFILE where completed = pipelines_count
select * from FLOWFILE where failed = 0 and completed < pipelines_count

config.comments: Process date is set by default to ETL_process_date context parameter.

entry.value: SELECT ${pipelines_count} AS pipelines_count, count(CASE WHEN state = 'SCHEDULED' THEN 0 END) AS scheduled, count(CASE WHEN state = 'RUNNING' THEN 0 END) AS now_running, count(CASE WHEN state = 'FAILED' THEN 0 END) AS failed, count(CASE WHEN state = 'COMPLETED' THEN 0 END) AS completed FROM (SELECT state FROM ( SELECT *, max(modified_datetime) OVER (PARTITION BY component_name, process_date) AS max_modified_datetime FROM etl_traffic_lights WHERE process_date = ${process_date} ) etl_max WHERE component_name IN (${pipelines_names}) AND modified_datetime = max_modified_datetime) state_summary

INSERT INTO monitoring.NiFi_process_status(source_system, target_system, load_id, rundate, usecase_name, dir_name, file_name, `rows`, step, status, start_ts, end_ts) VALUES('${source_system}', '${target_system}', ${load_id}, ${run_date}, '${usecase_name}', '${dir_name}', '${file_name}', ${row_count}, '${step}', '${status}', '${start_ts}', '${now():format("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss")}');
